[English] Flow waters of Loudwater against the Ringwraiths!

879
01:22:51,494 --> 01:22:54,643
[Sindarin] <i>Nîn o Chithaeglir, lasto beth daer!</i>
[English] Waters of the Misty Mountains, listen to the great word!

880
01:22:54,644 --> 01:22:58,024
[Sindarin] <i>Rimmo nîn Bruinen dan in Ulaer!</i>
[English] Flow waters of Loudwater against the Ringwraiths!

881
01:23:25,355 --> 01:23:27,794
{\an8} [English] ♫ What Grace... ♫

882
01:23:27,795 --> 01:23:30,195
No. No!

883
01:23:33,496 --> 01:23:34,156
Frodo, no.

884
01:23:34,157 --> 01:23:35,995
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...is given me... ♫

885
01:23:35,996 --> 01:23:38,196
Frodo, don't give in.

886
01:23:38,496 --> 01:23:40,396
Not now.

887
01:23:45,158 --> 01:23:51,495
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...let it pass... ♫

888
01:23:51,496 --> 01:23:53,896
What grace is given me...

889
01:23:54,596 --> 01:23:54,958
...let it pass to him.

890
01:23:54,959 --> 01:23:56,695
{\an8} [English] ♫ ...to him. ♫

891
01:23:56,696 --> 01:23:57,655
Let him be spared.

892
01:23:57,656 --> 01:23:59,496
{\an8} [English] ♫ Let him be spared. Mighty Valar, save him.  ♫

893
01:23:59,497 --> 01:24:01,397
Save him.

894
01:24:03,357 --> 01:24:07,447
[Sindarin] <i>Lasto beth nîn. Tolo dan nan galad.</i>
[English] Hear my voice. Come back to the light.

895
01:24:13,897 --> 01:24:18,897
- Where am I?
- You are in the house of Elrond.

896
01:24:19,497 --> 01:24:25,698
And it is 10 o'clock in the morning
on October 24th, if you want to know.

897
01:24:27,998 --> 01:24:31,598
- Gandalf!
- Yes, I'm here.

898
01:24:33,498 --> 01:24:36,398
And you're lucky to be here too.

899
01:24:37,098 --> 01:24:40,998
A few more hours and you would
have been beyond our aid.

900
01:24:41,398 --> 01:24:45,298
But you have some strength in you,
my dear Hobbit.

901
01:24:53,099 --> 01:24:55,499
What happened, Gandalf?

902
01:24:56,499 --> 01:25:01,799
- Why didn't you meet us?
- I am sorry, Frodo.

903
01:25:06,599 --> 01:25:08,299
I was delayed.

904
01:25:09,399 --> 01:25:13,399
A friendship with Saruman
is not lightly thrown aside.

905
01:25:17,700 --> 01:25:22,200
One ill turn deserves another. It is over.

906
01:25:22,700 --> 01:25:25,300
Embrace the power of the ring...

907
01:25:26,000 --> 01:25:28,400
...or embrace your own destruction!

908
01:25:30,800 --> 01:25:34,500
There is only one lord of the ring.

909
01:25:35,000 --> 01:25:38,800
Only one who can bend it to his will.

910
01:25:39,800 --> 01:25:43,601
And he does not share power.

911
01:25:58,001 --> 01:26:01,201
So you have chosen...death.

912
01:26:11,502 --> 01:26:15,102
Gandalf? What is it?

913
01:26:16,302 --> 01:26:18,002
Nothing, Frodo.

914
01:26:18,702 --> 01:26:20,602
Frodo!

915
01:26:22,002 --> 01:26:24,202
- Sam.
- Bless you, you're awake!

916
01:26:24,602 --> 01:26:27,202
Sam has hardly left your side.

917
01:26:27,602 --> 01:26:29,602
We were that worried about you.
Weren't we, Mr. Gandalf?

918
01:26:30,202 --> 01:26:35,103
By the skills of Lord Elrond,
you're beginning to mend.

919
01:26:36,703 --> 01:26:40,203
Welcome to Rivendell, Frodo Baggins.

920
01:27:28,405 --> 01:27:31,505
- Bilbo!
- Hello, Frodo, my lad.

921
01:27:31,905 --> 01:27:33,605
Bilbo.

922
01:27:38,505 --> 01:27:40,504
There and back again

923
01:27:40,505 --> 01:27:43,205
A hobbit's Tale, by Bilbo Baggins.''

924
01:27:46,405 --> 01:27:49,806
- This is wonderful.
- I meant to go back...

925
01:27:50,206 --> 01:27:53,906
...wonder at the powers of Mirkwood...

926
01:27:54,506 --> 01:27:56,706
...visit Lake-town...

927
01:27:57,006 --> 01:28:00,306
...see the Lonely Mountain again.

928
01:28:01,006 --> 01:28:05,606
But age, it seems, has finally caught up with me.

929
01:28:18,007 --> 01:28:19,707
I miss the Shire.

930
01:28:20,207 --> 01:28:25,107
I spent all my childhood pretending
I was off somewhere else.

931
01:28:25,607 --> 01:28:29,007
Off with you, on one of your adventures.

932
01:28:32,007 --> 01:28:35,507
But my own adventure turned out
to be quite different.

933
01:28:41,008 --> 01:28:44,008
I'm not like you, Bilbo.

934
01:28:45,408 --> 01:28:47,508
My dear boy.

935
01:28:51,808 --> 01:28:55,508
- Now, what have I forgotten?
- Packed already?

936
01:28:56,408 --> 01:28:58,108
No harm in being prepared.

937
01:28:58,408 --> 01:29:00,908
- I thought you wanted to see the elves.
- I do.

938
01:29:01,208 --> 01:29:03,908
- More than anything.
- I did.

939
01:29:04,308 --> 01:29:06,208
It's just....

940
01:29:07,009 --> 01:29:09,509
We did what Gandalf wanted, didn't we?

941
01:29:09,809 --> 01:29:13,309
We got the ring this far, to Rivendell.
And I thought...

942
01:29:13,809 --> 01:29:16,909
...seeing as how you're on the mend,
we'd be off soon.

943
01:29:17,209 --> 01:29:18,809
Off home.

944
01:29:23,009 --> 01:29:24,909
You are right, Sam.

945
01:29:27,209 --> 01:29:29,909
We did what we set out to do.

946
01:29:30,509 --> 01:29:33,010
The ring will be safe in Rivendell.

947
01:29:37,210 --> 01:29:39,510
I am ready to go home.

948
01:29:40,310 --> 01:29:42,210
His strength returns.

949
01:29:42,510 --> 01:29:48,010
That wound will never fully heal.
He will carry it the rest of his life.

950
01:29:48,910 --> 01:29:51,309
And yet to have come so far still bearing the ring...

951
01:29:51,310 --> 01:29:55,110
...the Hobbit has shown extraordinary
resilience to its evil.

952
01:29:55,510 --> 01:29:58,811
It is a burden he should never have had to bear.

953
01:29:59,111 --> 01:30:04,311
- We can ask no more of Frodo.
- Gandalf, the enemy is moving.

954
01:30:04,711 --> 01:30:09,211
Sauron's forces are massing in the East.
His eye is fixed on Rivendell.

955
01:30:09,611 --> 01:30:12,211
And Saruman, you tell me, has betrayed us.

956
01:30:12,611 --> 01:30:15,711
Our list of allies grows thin.

957
01:30:16,511 --> 01:30:19,211
His treachery runs deeper than you know.

958
01:30:19,511 --> 01:30:23,011
By foul craft, Saruman
has crossed orcs with goblin-men.

959
01:30:23,412 --> 01:30:25,712
He's breeding an army in the caverns of Isengard.

960
01:30:26,112 --> 01:30:30,512
An army that can move in sunlight
and cover great distance at speed.

961
01:30:30,912 --> 01:30:33,212
Saruman is coming for the ring.

962
01:30:33,712 --> 01:30:37,612
This evil cannot be concealed
by the power of the elves.

963
01:30:38,012 --> 01:30:42,212
We do not have the strength to
fight both Mordor and Isengard!

964
01:30:46,212 --> 01:30:47,212
Gandalf...

965
01:30:48,612 --> 01:30:51,013
...the ring cannot stay here.

966
01:31:10,713 --> 01:31:13,813
This peril belongs to all Middle-earth.

967
01:31:14,113 --> 01:31:16,814
They must decide now how to end it.

968
01:31:17,914 --> 01:31:21,314
The time of the elves is over.
My people are leaving these shores.

969
01:31:22,114 --> 01:31:25,614
Who will you look to when we've gone?
The dwarves?

970
01:31:26,014 --> 01:31:30,914
They hide in mountains seeking riches.
They care not for the troubles of others.

971
01:31:32,614 --> 01:31:35,414
It is in men that we must place our hope.

972
01:31:35,914 --> 01:31:37,514
Men?

973
01:31:38,514 --> 01:31:41,515
Men are weak. The race of men is failing.

974
01:31:41,915 --> 01:31:46,115
The blood of Numenor is all but spent,
its pride and dignity forgotten.

975
01:31:46,615 --> 01:31:50,015
It is because of men the ring survives.

976
01:31:50,415 --> 01:31:51,915
I was there, Gandalf.

977
01:31:52,715 --> 01:31:55,415
I was there 3000 years ago...

978
01:32:02,315 --> 01:32:04,615
... when Isildur took the ring.

979
01:32:04,915 --> 01:32:08,616
I was there the day the strength of men failed.

980
01:32:11,316 --> 01:32:13,816
Isildur, hurry! Follow me.

981
01:32:15,516 --> 01:32:19,016
I led Isildur into the heart of Mount Doom...

982
01:32:19,416 --> 01:32:22,815
...where the ring was forged,
the one place it could be destroyed.

983
01:32:22,816 --> 01:32:25,516
Cast it into the fire!

984
01:32:30,816 --> 01:32:34,417
- Destroy it!
- No.

985
01:32:35,917 --> 01:32:38,017
Isildur!

986
01:32:38,517 --> 01:32:43,117
It should have ended that day,
but evil was allowed to endure.

987
01:32:47,417 --> 01:32:51,517
Isildur kept the ring.
The line of kings is broken.

988
01:32:52,517 --> 01:32:56,117
There's no strength left in the world of men.

989
01:32:56,517 --> 01:33:01,118
- They're scattered, divided, leaderless.
- There is one who could unite them.

990
01:33:01,518 --> 01:33:04,718
One who could reclaim the throne of Gondor.

991
01:33:06,618 --> 01:33:10,218
He turned from that path a long time ago.

992
01:33:10,518 --> 01:33:12,618
He has chosen exile.

993
01:33:43,719 --> 01:33:45,619
You are no elf.

994
01:33:45,919 --> 01:33:47,919
Men of the South are welcome here.

995
01:33:48,620 --> 01:33:52,020
- Who are you?
- I am a friend to Gandalf the Grey.

996
01:33:53,620 --> 01:33:56,320
Then we are here on common purpose...

997
01:33:56,720 --> 01:33:58,120
...friend.

998
01:34:13,520 --> 01:34:16,321
The shards of Narsil.

999
01:34:19,921 --> 01:34:24,121
The blade that cut the ring from Sauron's hand.

1000
01:34:27,221 --> 01:34:29,421
It's still sharp.

1001
01:34:38,421 --> 01:34:41,322
But no more than a broken heirloom.

1002
01:35:08,323 --> 01:35:11,323
Why do you fear the past?

1003
01:35:12,223 --> 01:35:17,323
You are Isildur's heir, not Isildur himseIf.

1004
01:35:17,823 --> 01:35:21,123
You are not bound to his fate.

1005
01:35:21,723 --> 01:35:25,523
The same blood flows in my veins.

1006
01:35:28,723 --> 01:35:31,224
The same weakness.

1007
01:35:34,024 --> 01:35:36,724
Your time will come.

1008
01:35:37,024 --> 01:35:41,224
You will face the same evil.
And you will defeat it.

1009
01:35:44,084 --> 01:35:46,794
[Sindarin] <i>A si i-Dhúath ú-orthor, Aragorn.</i>
[English] The shadow does not hold sway yet, Aragorn.

1010
01:35:47,784 --> 01:35:51,374
[Sindarin] <i>Ú or le a ú or nin.</i>
[English] Not over you, not over me.

1011
01:36:02,535 --> 01:36:05,775
[Sindarin] <i>Renich i lú i erui govannem?</i>
[English] Do you remember when we first met?

1012
01:36:09,265 --> 01:36:13,295
[Sindarin] <i>Nauthannen i ned ôl reniannen.</i>
[English] I thought I had strayed into a dream.

1013
01:36:14,195 --> 01:36:16,875
[Sindarin] <i>Gwenwin in enninath.</i>
[English] Long years have passed.

1014
01:36:17,915 --> 01:36:21,575
[Sindarin] <i>Ú-'arnech in naeth i si celich.</i>
[English] You did not wear the troubles you carry now.

1015
01:36:23,416 --> 01:36:25,716
[Sindarin] <i>Renich i beth i pennen?</i>
[English] Do you remember what I told you?

1016
01:36:31,926 --> 01:36:34,526
You said you'd bind yourself to me...

1017
01:36:36,726 --> 01:36:41,426
...forsaking the immortal life of your people.

1018
01:36:42,726 --> 01:36:44,625
And to that I hold.

1019
01:36:44,626 --> 01:36:48,327
I would rather share one lifetime with you...

1020
01:36:48,827 --> 01:36:52,427
...than face all the ages of this world alone.

1021
01:37:01,327 --> 01:37:04,627
I choose a mortal life.

1022
01:37:06,127 --> 01:37:10,227
- You cannot give me this.
- It is mine to give to whom I will...

1023
01:37:13,628 --> 01:37:16,028
...like my heart.

1024
01:37:31,928 --> 01:37:35,528
Strangers from distant lands, friends of old...

1025
01:37:35,928 --> 01:37:39,629
...you've been summoned here
to answer the threat of Mordor.

1026
01:37:40,429 --> 01:37:45,129
Middle-earth stands upon the brink of destruction.
None can escape it.

1027
01:37:45,529 --> 01:37:48,929
You will unite, or you will fall.

1028
01:37:49,329 --> 01:37:53,429
Each race is bound to this fate, this one doom.

1029
01:37:55,429 --> 01:37:58,729
Bring forth the ring, Frodo.

1030
01:38:13,030 --> 01:38:14,630
So it is true.

1031
01:38:24,430 --> 01:38:25,930
<i>The ring of power...</i>

1032
01:38:28,030 --> 01:38:29,530
<i>The doom of men...</i>

1033
01:38:32,131 --> 01:38:34,131
In a dream...

1034
01:38:35,931 --> 01:38:39,031
...I saw the eastern sky grow dark...

1035
01:38:39,331 --> 01:38:41,031
...but in the West a pale light lingered.

1036
01:38:41,831 --> 01:38:43,631
A voice was crying:

1037
01:38:43,931 --> 01:38:46,731
"Your doom is near at hand.

1038
01:38:47,931 --> 01:38:50,531
Isildur's bane is found."

1039
01:38:52,661 --> 01:38:54,061
(The Ring)
[Black Speech] <i>Sherkuk-ishi</i>
[English] In your blood

1040
01:38:54,531 --> 01:38:56,332
Isildur s bane.

1041
01:38:56,932 --> 01:38:57,192
Boromir!

1042
01:38:57,193 --> 01:38:58,541
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1043
01:38:58,542 --> 01:39:00,961
{\an8} (The Ring)
{\an8} [Black Speech] <i>Shre nazg golugranu kilmi-nudu...</i>
{\an8} [English] Three Rings for the Elven-kings under the sky...

1044
01:39:00,962 --> 01:39:04,495
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul...</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them...

1045
01:39:04,496 --> 01:39:04,881
{\an8} (The Ring)
{\an8} [Black Speech] <i>Ombi kuzd-durbagu... shirku</i>
{\an8} [English] Seven for the Dwarf-lords... blood

1046
01:39:04,882 --> 01:39:08,052
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg thrakatulûk...</i>
[English] ...One ring to bring them all...

1047
01:39:09,076 --> 01:39:10,961
{\an8} (The Ring)
{\an8} [Black Speech] <i>Ash Burz-Durbagu burzum-ishi...</i>
{\an8} [English] One for the Dark lord on his dark throne...

1048
01:39:10,962 --> 01:39:15,282
(Gandalf)
[Black Speech] <i>...Agh burzum-ishi krimpatul.</i>
[English] ...and in the darkness bind them.

1049
01:39:21,432 --> 01:39:25,133
Never before has any voice uttered the
words of that tongue here in Imladris.

1050
01:39:25,533 --> 01:39:29,033
I do not ask your pardon, Master Elrond...

1051
01:39:29,333 --> 01:39:31,333
...for the black speech of Mordor...

1052
01:39:31,733 --> 01:39:33,033
...may yet be heard...

1053
01:39:33,333 --> 01:39:36,133
...in every corner of the West!

1054
01:39:36,433 --> 01:39:39,033
The ring is altogether evil.

1055
01:39:39,533 --> 01:39:40,933
It is a gift.

1056
01:39:41,733 --> 01:39:43,633
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

1057
01:39:44,333 --> 01:39:46,333
Why not use this ring?

1058
01:39:46,633 --> 01:39:49,334
Long has my father, the Steward of Gondor...

1059
01:39:49,634 --> 01:39:53,734
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.
By the blood of our people...

1060
01:39:54,234 --> 01:39:56,334
...are your lands kept safe.

1061
01:39:58,134 --> 01:40:02,334
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.
Let us use it against him.

1062
01:40:02,734 --> 01:40:06,334
You cannot wield it. None of us can.

1063
01:40:07,134 --> 01:40:11,034
The one ring answers to Sauron alone.
It has no other master.

1064
01:40:11,434 --> 01:40:14,835
And what would a ranger know of this matter?

1065
01:40:15,135 --> 01:40:17,035
This is no mere ranger.

1066
01:40:18,135 --> 01:40:21,635
He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

1067
01:40:22,335 --> 01:40:25,135
You owe him your allegiance.

1068
01:40:29,335 --> 01:40:31,235
Aragorn.

1069
01:40:33,035 --> 01:40:35,835
This is Isildur s heir?

1070
01:40:38,235 --> 01:40:40,936
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

1071
01:40:42,416 --> 01:40:44,316
[Sindarin] <i>Havo dad, Legolas.</i>
[English] Sit down, Legolas.

1072
01:40:47,836 --> 01:40:50,636
Gondor has no king.

1073
01:40:52,636 --> 01:40:54,236
Gondor needs no king.

1074
01:41:00,936 --> 01:41:04,437
Aragorn is right. We cannot use it.

1075
01:41:05,637 --> 01:41:08,937
You have only one choice.

1076
01:41:09,237 --> 01:41:11,537
The ring must be destroyed.

1077
01:41:16,837 --> 01:41:19,337
What are we waiting for?

1078
01:41:24,587 --> 01:41:29,699
[Black Speech] <i>Daghburz-ishi makha, ghurarmu shirku.</i>
[English] In the land of Mordor, a sacrifice of blood.

1079
01:41:31,538 --> 01:41:34,438
The ring cannot be destroyed, Gimli, son of Gloin...

1080
01:41:34,838 --> 01:41:38,938
...by any craft that we here possess.

1081
01:41:39,638 --> 01:41:43,538
The ring was made in the fires of Mount Doom.

1082
01:41:44,038 --> 01:41:47,638
Only there can it be unmade.

1083
01:41:48,938 --> 01:41:51,338
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

1084
01:41:51,638 --> 01:41:55,342
...and cast back into the fiery
chasm from whence it came.

1085
01:41:55,343 --> 01:41:58,379
[Black Speech] <i>Makha gulshu darulu.</i>
[English] Where the Shadows lie.

1086
01:41:58,439 --> 01:42:00,539
One of you...

1087
01:42:01,139 --> 01:42:03,239
...must do this.

1088
01:42:06,239 --> 01:42:09,839
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

1089
01:42:10,839 --> 01:42:14,339
Its black gates are guarded by more than just orcs.

1090
01:42:15,239 --> 01:42:19,239
There is evil there that does not sleep.

1091
01:42:19,639 --> 01:42:23,740
The great eye is ever-watchful.

1092
01:42:24,640 --> 01:42:26,540
It is a barren wasteland...

1093
01:42:26,940 --> 01:42:30,240
...riddled with fire, and ash and dust.

1094
01:42:30,640 --> 01:42:34,440
The very air you breathe is a poisonous fume.

1095
01:42:34,740 --> 01:42:38,840
Not with 10,000 men could you do this.
It is folly.

1096
01:42:39,240 --> 01:42:43,540
Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond has said?
The ring must be destroyed.

1097
01:42:43,940 --> 01:42:46,340
And I suppose you think you are the one to do it!

1098
01:42:46,640 --> 01:42:51,141
And if we fail, what then? What happens
when Sauron takes back what is his?

1099
01:42:51,541 --> 01:42:56,641
I will be dead before I see the
ring in the hands of an elf!

1100
01:42:58,841 --> 01:43:01,241
Never trust an elf!

1101
01:43:02,541 --> 01:43:08,141
Do you not understand? While you bicker
amongst yourselves, Sauron's power grows!

1102
01:43:08,641 --> 01:43:11,441
None can escape it!
You'll all be destroyed!

1103
01:43:11,991 --> 01:43:14,771
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1104
01:43:14,772 --> 01:43:17,282
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul.</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them.

1105
01:43:17,292 --> 01:43:19,382
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1106
01:43:19,392 --> 01:43:21,491
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul.</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them.

1107
01:43:21,492 --> 01:43:23,482
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1108
01:43:23,492 --> 01:43:25,691
[Black Speech] <i>...Ash nazg gimbatul.</i>
[English] ...One ring to find them.

1109
01:43:25,692 --> 01:43:27,592
[Black Speech] <i>Ash nazg durbatulûk...</i>
[English] One ring to rule them all...

1110
01:43:30,242 --> 01:43:32,242
I will take it.

1111
01:43:34,542 --> 01:43:37,042
I will take it.

1112
01:43:42,843 --> 01:43:45,843
I will take the ring to Mordor.

1113
01:43:54,143 --> 01:43:55,243
Though...

1114
01:43:58,443 --> 01:44:00,243
...I do not know the way.

1115
01:44:02,243 --> 01:44:06,344
I will help you bear this burden, Frodo Baggins...

1116
01:44:06,744 --> 01:44:10,044
...as long as it is yours to bear.

1117
01:44:11,244 --> 01:44:14,244
If by my life or death I can protect you...

1118
01:44:15,044 --> 01:44:16,344
...I will.

1119
01:44:19,644 --> 01:44:21,844
You have my sword.

1120
01:44:23,744 --> 01:44:25,744
And you have my bow.

1121
01:44:26,444 --> 01:44:28,744
And my ax.

1122
01:44:35,945 --> 01:44:38,745
You carry the fates of us all, little one.

1123
01:44:40,945 --> 01:44:44,445
If this is indeed the will of the Council...

1124
01:44:45,145 --> 01:44:47,545
...then Gondor will see it done.

1125
01:44:50,145 --> 01:44:54,745
- Mr. Frodo's not going anywhere without me.
- No indeed it is hardly possible to separate you...

1126
01:44:55,146 --> 01:44:59,846
...even when he is summoned to a
secret council and you are not.

1127
01:45:00,546 --> 01:45:02,346
Oy. We're coming too!

1128
01:45:04,546 --> 01:45:07,245
You'll have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us.

1129
01:45:07,246 --> 01:45:10,646
Anyway, you need people
of intelligence on this sort of...

1130
01:45:11,146 --> 01:45:12,345
...mission.

1131
01:45:12,346 --> 01:45:13,896
Quest.

1132
01:45:14,396 --> 01:45:15,396
Thing.

1133
01:45:17,196 --> 01:45:19,896
Well, that rules you out, Pip.

1134
01:45:21,597 --> 01:45:23,397
Nine companions.

1135
01:45:25,197 --> 01:45:26,997
So be it.

1136
01:45:27,397 --> 01:45:30,397
You shall be: The Fellowship of the Ring.

1137
01:45:31,097 --> 01:45:32,897
Great!

1138
01:45:33,297 --> 01:45:35,397
Where are we going?

